It feels like it is lost some of its oomph compared to when it was in NEXT.
It looks much better than the NEXT one-shot!
It is pretty good, but it is going to take some work to keep it from getting boring if it gets serialized.
I am excited to see what happens next.
It is perfect for a serialization.
I am looking forward to tomorrow's serialization committee!
It is a pleasure to meet you.
We have been dating since middle school, and now we are in the same college.
We can practice the greeting after we get serialized!
Besides, I do not even know what your dad's like!
He is the CEO of a company, is not he?
Yeah, but it is only a small real estate company in Yakusa.
So you are the only daughter of a CEO?
He also teaches karate in a nearby dojo.
We have got both a serialization and a marriage riding on what happens today.
I am at a crossroads in life.
This is how you get registered!
We can only do that after we get serialized and get permission from our parents!
It is fine to get the form in advance!
It is all about a man's technique!
Well, I mean his manga technique.
Katou, what do you think of a guy who has technique?
I am talking about manga, of course.
Um, I have not mentioned this,
but Business Boy Kenichi might be canceled in today's serialization meeting.
If it does end, we will have to part ways with each other again.
But even if it ends, we can still see each other, right?
Yeah, since we have gotten to know each other, we could talk on the phone sometimes.
Well, meeting up would be kind of weird... we are not dating, or anything.
Natsumi, is that all you felt for me?
R-Right, there is no way you would have feelings for me...
Please do not joke about that.
But I was pretty serious about you.
Please do not have this conversation here!
This is the first time I have seen Takahama get angry.
Since he is this irritated, it must mean Business Boy Kenichi is in deep trouble.
Miura, do not be so uptight.
Only eight storyboards were submitted, so even if only two pass, that means you already have a 25 chance.
And judging by Tanto's quality, I would say it is a 50 chance.
Arai's is definitely in, so if two new ones start up, you will only have a 1 in 7 chance of being the other one.
Yamahisa, that is enough out of you.
And I told Ashirogi that they only needed three solid chapters to pass for sure...
If they do not get serialized, then...
Time of Blue Leaves will start its serialization in the second issue of the new year!
Everyone thinks it is much better than the NEXT one-shot.
It is like a surprise comeback!
It is all thanks to Fukuda and everyone...
I have to thank them properly.
Unlike in your previous series where you only did the manuscript,
this time you will need a few assistants to help you.
Can they work at your home?
But I would like all female assistants, if possible.
I will arrange it as quickly as possible.
Miura, I do not need to know what is starting.
Time of Blue Leaves... that is Aoki...
You two can leave for today.
I want to be alone for a while.
Hey, do not get so down.
We just have to make it even better and submit it to the next committee.
It will definitely pass next time...
But you said it would pass as long as we had three chapters.
They just have really high expectations for you guys.
You could even say it was for the best...
Ah, sorry, but Business Boy Kenichi is ending, so I have to go meet with Takahama.
I knew getting a serialization was not going to be that easy.
Takagi, you did not want to get married, so you let the quality slip!
It concerns me that Takahama's also ended.
We have got the same editor.
But it was thanks to Miura that we got 1st place in NEXT!
We have got no choice but to trust him!
Right, we will definitely get serialized next time.
Let us have faith in that and keep our heads up!
Katou, before it ends, there is something I want to clarify...
I cannot have a special relationship with you.
No, it will only be for work.
If I say I will just be an assistant...
I heard you got serialized, and I thought you might be needing assistants.
Not drawing the art, just assisting...
I think there is something else you should say to me before that.
But even if you apologized, I have decided that all of my assistants will be female,
so there would not be much of a point.
The serialization I was assisting with is ending,
and Natsumi and I will part ways when it is over...
Please do not call me again.
I told him I would not have a special relationship with him.
Nakai's going back to the country?!
Yeah, I just called him, and he said he is quitting manga and going back home!
Because he was rejected by Katou?
Even though he is that kind of person, there are not many people with art as good as his.
We should try to stop him...
So it is Mashiro this time?
Why are you going back home?
That art led me down the wrong path.
There is no use trying to stop me.
Tomorrow, I am clearing out everything and leaving.
I do not feel like stopping him.
He is done some bad stuff.
I am going home to think of some gags.
We cannot do anything unless Nakai works up some resolve himself.
Anything we try would just be butting into his business, and would not accomplish anything.
I told him never to call me again yesterday.
My hometown's a place called Akita.
I will send you a bunch of apples.
You are the one who taught me the basics of backgrounds!
Then I am glad I drew manga, if only for that.
Like you, all I can do is draw!
Do not... do not give up on your dream!
But like I said yesterday, I do not have the right to draw manga anymore.
Thank you for your help with hideout door.
I am sorry for all the trouble I caused you.
You will not let it end like this, will you?!
It does better than I thought as a shounen manga.
It is all thanks to your coaching.
I just did as you told me.
Even though you said it was only going to be a 45 page one-shot?
I want to read the rest now.
Stick to the basics that I have taught you,
but this time, I want to you write freely.
Will something I come up with on my own be acceptable?
Of course, I will look at it and point out the parts that need fixing.
If it is bad, I will tell you why.
At any rate, I want to see how far you can get on your own.
She did everything I told her.
What can we fix in this storyboard?
That is what we are going to discuss in the meeting today, right?
There is a limit to how many gags we can put in.
If it needs any changing, would not it be better to change the whole plot?
If only eight storyboards were submitted this time, there will be a lot more next time.
And only two or three get serialized.
At least now I know that Miura's Absolutely!
Will we really make it with him as our editor?
We will not make it on time if we do not leave now!
Aida, what do you think the best way to rework this storyboard would be?
I cannot think of any way to improve it.
Then just submit it to the next committee as-is.
Just tell them what the committee's opinions were.
Since Business Boy Kenichi ended, I am not editing any serialized manga.
I have to get serialized at the next committee...
Can I talk to you for a minute?
Basically, the part you did in the one-shot lost its impact in the serialization storyboard.
This will always happen, especially with gag manga.
We have to power it up!
We just need to think about how to do it!
Even if you say power it up, we have exhausted the possibilities with the characters.
You said that if it ever became a battle manga, you would write in an evil inventor.
Oh, that is a rival, is not it?
Leave the first chapter as is...
and introduce the evil inventor in the second!
I believe you should also be present.
I am currently in a meeting with Ashirogi on the first floor,
but should I come up right now?
Why did he go straight to the Chief Editor and not Miura?
Takahama has asked me to change his editor.
Because he will not let me draw what I want.
He will not let me draw what I want...
is an admission that you do not have any talent.
If what you wanted to draw produced an excellent shounen manga,
then it would be accepted as-is.
Because it is not, it means that you do not have the ability to do so.
He will not let me draw what I want...
It does seems like an excuse.
I believe that an author who blames
the editing department or his editor for a work that does not produce results
If you disagree with your editor and believe you are right no matter what,
then draw a shounen manga that will force him to agree.
There are works that have succeeded that way.
In a way, those works are the real thing.
I will not change your editor.
It is not because you are a newcomer.
I will not make exceptions, even for great and influential authors.
If you truly cannot get along with Miura,
then you can draw for another magazine.
I will take care of ending the contract.
Takahama, if you have issues with me, please tell me directly.
I will fix what I am doing wrong.
The Chief Editor was scary today.
Let us stop putting all the blame on our editor.
I think I have heard the name Akina Aiko somewhere before...
She is this year's Pleiades amateur contest winner.
So why is she writing a manga manuscript?
Well, she may be a rival in terms of manuscript writing,
but who is doing the art?
No, someone who can draw it at a level that can compete with Ashirogi Muto.
Are they going to fight after this?
It ended at a good place, too.
Are you making this into a one-shot?
It has not been decided yet.
I am looking for any artist who can draw it well.
You cannot take a break from CROW.
Neglect it in any way, and the deal's off!
I do not care about the character designs right now.
Can you make a storyboard for me?
Hey, were you listening to me?
A circle here, a circle there...
Drawing an interesting story I could have never come up with is fun, too!
And right here, hot hot hot...
I thought it would make the story better, but not by this much!
Wait, but what will happen if this is accepted?
Niizuma, I am going to have the higher ups take a look at this.
But only on the condition that you keep doing CROW and keep the quality up.
But if I am going to draw it...
I will only do it as a serialization.
I am already having her write a second chapter.
I will have her write a third and submit it to the next serialization committee.
Akina's been Takagi's rival since middle school.
If we do this, it will definitely fire up Ashirogi Muto!
Yuujirou, I definitely want this to get serialized.
But two works by the same author getting serialized at the same time!?
It is fine, it just has not happened before.
He will have an impossible schedule!
But you know I can make a storyboard in a day, and a manuscript in two!
Damn, he can do it if we get more assistants.
And she will be the one writing the manuscripts, anyway.
It will be a piece of cake!
How are we going to explain this to the higher-ups?
Niizuma, can you draw this as if you were someone else?
It is fine as long as they do not know I am drawing it?
A new, outstanding artist has appeared.
We will pass it out with him using a pen name, and if it passes at the committee, reveal the truth.
If it passes and we reveal that it was Niizuma, they will have no choice but to do it.
Hattori, was this your aim from the beginning?
No, I would never thought it would get this far.
From the chicken comes an egg, from the egg comes a chicken!
It is getting Niizuma fired up again, and it will not interfere with CROW.
If we have authors with a strong sense of rivalry compete with each other,
it could be a good thing for Jack.
If this works, I will get promoted to lead editor!
Maybe even put on the serialization committee...
Hattori, if this goes well, let us split the credit.
Until this passes at the committee, it will be a secret project.
I will be the first manga author with two serializations in Jack!
Sounds like a pretty scary development.
I will bring you to your knees!
It might be a driving force for any dream!
